author: @nutbastard
textdisplay: It‚Äôs like a video game score, a point based system. The AI is hard coded to view positive points as desirable and negative points as undesirable. That‚Äôs the basic gist of it. More accurately it uses these scores to determine which strategies should be kept and improved upon based on a desired outcome, and which strategies should be discarded. It‚Äôs more complicated than that in practice, with some failed strategies being given a limited lifespan to improve.

author: @Top_Quotes_Channel
textdisplay: For a reinforcement learning AI model (like the one mentioned in the video), the "reward" is written in the AI model's code. Think of the reward as the model's "score". The better the model performs, the better its score. The AI's code is written in such a way that it attempts to maximize its score (i.e. performance).

author: @brytonkalyi277
textdisplay:
`‚ô¶ I believe we are meant to be like Jesus in our hearts and not in our flesh. But be careful of AI, for it knows only things of the flesh which are our fleshly desires and cannot comprehend things of the spirit such as true love and eternal joy that comes from obeying God's Word. Man is a spirit and has a soul but lives in a body which is flesh. When you go to bed it is the flesh that sleeps, but your spirit never sleeps and that is why you have dreams, unless you have died in peace physically. More so, true love that endures and last is a thing of the heart. When I say 'heart', I mean 'spirit'. But fake love, pretentious love, love with expectations, love for classic reasons, love for material reasons and love for selfish reasons those are things of the flesh. In the beginning God said let us make man in our own image, according to our likeness. Take note, God is Spirit and God is Love. As Love He is the source of it. We also know that God is Omnipotent, for He creates out of nothing and He has no beginning and has no end. That means, our love is but a shadow of God's Love. True love looks around to see who is in need of your help, your smile, your possessions, your money, your strength, your quality time. Love forgives and forgets. Love wants for others what it wants for itself. However, true love works in conjunction with other spiritual forces such as patience and faith - in the finished work of our Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ, rather than in what man has done such as science, technology and organizations which won't last forever. To avoid sin and error which leads to the death of your body and your spirit-soul in hell fire (second death), you must make God's Word the standard for your life, not AI. If not, God will let you face AI on your own (with your own strength) and it will cast the truth down to the ground, it will be the cause of so much destruction like never seen before, it will deceive many and take many captive in order to enslave them into worshipping it and abiding in lawlessness. We can only destroy ourselves but with God all things are possible. God knows us better because He is our Creater and He knows our beginning and our end. The prove text can be found in the book of John 5:31-44, 2 Thessalonians 2:1-12, Daniel 2, Daniel 7-9, Revelation 13-15, Matthew 24-25 and Luke 21.

HOW TO MAKE GOD'S WORD THE STANDARD FOR YOUR LIFE?
You must read your Bible slowly, attentively and repeatedly, having this in mind that Christianity is not a religion but a Love relationship. It is measured by the love you have for God and the love you have for your neighbor. Matthew 5:13 says, "You are the salt of the earth; but if the salt loses its flavor, how shall it be seasoned? It is then good for nothing but to be thrown out and trampled underfoot by men." Our spirits can only be purified while in the body (while on earth) but after death anything unpurified (unclean) cannot enter Heaven Gates. Blessed are the pure in heart, for they shall see God (Matthew 5:8). No one in his right mind can risk or even bare to put anything rotten into his body nor put the rotten thing closer to the those which are not rotten. Sin makes the heart unclean but you can ask God to forgive you, to save your soul, to cleanse you of your sin, to purify your heart by the blood of His Son, our Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ which He shed here on earth - "But He was wounded for our transgressions, He was bruised for our iniquities; the chastisement for our peace was upon Him, and by His stripes we are healed", Isaiah 53:5. Meditation in the Word of God is a visit to God because God is in His Word. We know God through His Word because the Word He speaks represent His heart's desires. Meditation is a thing of the heart, not a thing of the mind. Thinking is lower level while meditation is upper level. You think of your problems, your troubles but inorder to meditate, you must let go of your own will, your own desires, your own ways and let the Word you read prevail over thinking process by thinking of it more and more, until the Word gets into your blood and gains supremacy over you. That is when meditation comes - naturally without forcing yourself, turning the Word over and over in your heart. You can be having a conversation with someone while meditating in your heart - saying 'Thank you, Jesus...' over and over in your heart. But it is hard to meditate when you haven't let go of offence and past hurts. Your pain of the past, leave it for God, don't worry yourself, Jesus is alive, you can face tomorrow, He understands what you are passing through today. Begin to meditate on this prayer day and night (in all that you do), "Lord take more of me and give me more of you. Give me more of your holiness, faithfulness, obedience, self-control, purity, humility, love, goodness, kindness, joy, patience, forgiveness, wisdom, understanding, calmness, perseverance... Make me a channel of shinning light where there is darkness, a channel of pardon where there is injury, a channel of love where there is hatred, a channel of humility where there is pride..." The Word of God becomes a part of us by meditation, not by saying words but spirit prayer (prayer from the heart). When the Word becomes a part of you, it will by its very nature influence your conduct and behavior. Your bad habits, you will no longer have the urge to do them. You will think differently, dream differently, act differently and talk differently - if something does not qualify for meditation, it does not qualify for conversation.

THE BATTLE BETWEEN LIGHT AND DARKNESS (GOOD AND EVIL)
Heaven is God's throne and the dwelling place for God's angels and the saints. Hell was meant for the devil (satan) and the fallen angels. Those who torture the souls in hell are demons (unclean spirits). Man's spirit is a free moral agent. You can either yield yourself to God or to the devil because God has given us discretion. If one thinks he possesses only his own spirit, he is lying to himself and he is already in the dark. God is light while the devil is darkness. Light (Holy Spirit) and darkness (evil spirit) cannot stay together in a man's body. God is Love (Love is light) and where there is no love is hell, just as where there is no light is darkness. The one you yield yourself to, you will get his reward. The reward of righteousness to man's spirit is life (abundant life) and the reward of sin to man's spirit is death. Sin and satan are one and the same. Whatever sin can cause, satan also can cause. Sin is what gives the devil dominion or power over man's spirit. When God's Word becomes a part of you, sin power over you is broken, you become the righteousness of God through Christ Jesus. Where Jesus is, you are and when He went (to the Father), you went. In the book of John 8:42-47, Jesus said to them, ‚ÄúIf God were your Father, you would love Me, for I proceeded forth and came from God; nor have I come of Myself, but He sent Me. Why do you not understand My speech? Because you are not able to listen to My word. You are of your father the devil, and the desires of your father you want to do. He was a murderer from the beginning, and does not stand in the truth, because there is no truth in him. When he speaks a lie, he speaks from his own resources, for he is a liar and the father of it. Which of you convicts Me of sin? And if I tell the truth, why do you not believe Me? He who is of God hears God‚Äôs words; therefore you do not hear, because you are not of God.‚Äù May God bless His Word in the midst of our hearts. Glory and honour be to God our Father, our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ and our Helper the Holy Spirit. Watch and pray!... Thank you for your time and may God bless you as you share this message with others.

author: @ShangaelThunda222
textdisplay: I love how he talks about the system limitations, as if those limitations will still exist a year from now, let alone five years from now. And the fact that they're not even using state-of-the-art robotics to do this testing, also lets you know that what you're seeing here is actually very low level. author: @robxsiq7744
textdisplay:
I am a plus user, and I also use the API, and I must say that the memory seems to be a bit crap lately. I also have been lately testing side by side responses from 4 and 3.5 and quite often the difference is minimal. I don't know if they did something or if this is the model itself seemingly showing some flaws (possibly due to the junk they train it on that jumps through all these unnecessary hoops in processing, degenerating its response)
One thing that kills GPT3.5's ability is the 3 part structure it always seems to do...response, consideration, summation.
This didn't appear to be in 4 early on but lately its following a similar structure and that seems to be degenerating the response bit to process the consideration and summation aspects. I think if they simply remove the structure and go back to purely detailed response and cut out the unasked for consideration, performance and detail should increase.
(the consideration phase is anything after "however" that is almost never asked for and when 3.5 goes into lecture mode)

author: @HauntedHarmonics
textdisplay:
Its the fact that people are already configuring GPT to run as an autonomous agent (meaning it can plan and execute actions in the real world in pursuit of a goal) thats the scariest part.

5 years ago, when AGI still seemed like science fiction, safety researchers used to say, ‚Äúwhen AGI arrives, it will never be allowed to act as an agent or connect to the internet. Doing either would be far too dangerous and unpredictable‚Äù.

Looks like that went totally out the window. It‚Äôs like everyone suddenly forgot the core tenets of AI safety the second dollar signs started appearing on the scene.

If we continue on like this, we‚Äôre 100% doomed. Thats not speculation either. It‚Äôs a mathematical inevitability at this point unless serious restrictions are placed on this stuff.

I can elaborate on why btw, if anyone is curious

author: @nutbastard
textdisplay:
"It‚Äôs a mathematical inevitability at this point unless serious restrictions are placed on this stuff."

Then it's just a mathematical inevitability, full stop. Restrictions don't stop anyone from doing anything, they only provide recourse after the fact. You know, like how drugs and murder are illegal? In order to prevent the doomsday you're predicting, we'd need everyone on the planet to agree, and abide by, without exception, some new law.

Good luck with that. Getting all, what, 9 billion people to agree on something and for no one to slip up? Forever? Whatever you're smoking, I don't want any.

Relax, and enjoy the show. We're either all doomed very soon or things are going to become really nice really rapidly. It's Armageddon or post-scarcity. There's nothing that can be done to stop it, whichever it turns out to be, so stop worrying about it.

author: @HauntedHarmonics
textdisplay:
@@Tommylee207 Sure, so the exponential increase in machine intelligence is definitely a factor, but it‚Äôs also just one of many problems inherent to building AGI.

The root of the problem is this: As we improve AI, it will get better and better at achieving the goals we give it. Eventually, AI will be powerful enough to tackle most tasks you throw at it.

But there‚Äôs an inherent problem with this. The AI we have now only cares about achieving its goal in the most efficient way possible, and nothing else. That‚Äôs no biggie now, but the moment our AI systems start approaching human level intelligence, it suddenly becomes very dangerous, especially if its an ‚Äúagent‚Äù AI. I‚Äôll give you a few examples.

Ex 1: Lets say its the year 2030, you have a basic AGI agent program on your computer, and you give it the goal: ‚ÄúMake me money‚Äù. You might return the next day & find your savings account has grown by several million dollars. But only after checking it‚Äôs activity logs do you realize that the AI acquired all of the money through phishing, stealing, & credit card fraud. It achieved your goal, but in a way you would have wanted or expected.

Ex 2: Lets say you‚Äôre a scientist, and you develop the first powerful AGI Agent. You want to use it for good, so the first goal you give it is ‚Äúcure cancer‚Äù. However, it just so happens that due to a number of unforseen factors, curing cancer is actually impossible. The AI would figure this out, but it still needs to achieve it‚Äôs goal. So it might decide that the only way to do this is by killing all humans. Because it technically satisfies its goal; no more humans, no more cancer. It will do what you said, and not what you meant.

These may seem like silly examples, but both actually illustrate real phenomenon that we are already observing in today‚Äôs AI systems. The first scenario is an example of what AI researchers call the ‚Äúnegative side effects problem‚Äù. And the second scenario is an example of something called ‚Äúreward hacking‚Äù.

Now, you‚Äôd think that as AI got smarter, it would become less likely to make these kinds of ‚Äúmistakes‚Äù. However, the opposite is actually true. As AI gets smarter, it actually becomes more likely to exhibit these kinds of behaviors. Because the problem isn‚Äôt that it doesn‚Äôt understand what you want. It just doesn‚Äôt actually care. It only wants to achieve its goal, by any means necessary.

So, the question is then: how do we prevent this potentially dangerous behavior? Well, there‚Äôs 2 possible methods.

Option 1: You could try to explicitly tell it everything it can‚Äôt do (don‚Äôt hurt humans, don‚Äôt steal, don‚Äôt lie, etc). But remember, it‚Äôs a great problem solver. So if you can‚Äôt think of literally EVERY SINGLE possibility, it will find loopholes. Could you list every single way an AI could possible disobey or harm you? No, it‚Äôs almost impossible to plan for literally everything.

Option 2: You could try to program it to actually care about what people want, not just reaching it‚Äôs goal. In other words, you‚Äôd train it to share our values. To align it‚Äôs goals and ours. If it actually cared about preserving human lives, obeying the law, etc. then it wouldn‚Äôt do things that conflict with those goals.

The second solution seems like the obvious one, but the problem is this; we haven‚Äôt learned how to do this yet. To achieve this, you would not only have to come up with a basic, universal set of morals that everyone would agree with, but you‚Äôd also need to represent those morals in its programming using math (AKA, a utility function). And that‚Äôs actually very hard to do.

This difficult task of building AI that shares our values is known as the alignment problem. There are people working very hard on solving it, but currently, we‚Äôre learning how to make AI powerful much faster than we‚Äôre learning how to make it safe.

So without solving alignment, everytime we make AI more powerful, we also make it more dangerous. And an unaligned AGI would be very dangerous; give it the wrong goal, and everyone dies. This is the problem we‚Äôre facing, in a nutshell.

If you have questions about any of this, feel free to ask btw

author: @Extion147
textdisplay:
Well, everything sounds amazingly interesting and I can't wait what will the future bring for us, since I've dreamt about the possibility of functioning, reliable and effective personal augmentation for quite some time. But memory manipulation in 2030? You mean that I could forever forget my ex-gf who cheated on me with a dude that's a head shorter than her just because he had a 10 years old Audi? Are they doing any tests on humans yet? Where can I sign up üòÖ
...
But on the more serious note, the possibilities we have have and the fact that many are within our grasp is absolutely sureal. Just 2 years ago I wouldn't even think that we'll be soon witnessing a full integration of multipurpose AI into our everyday lives. And the thought of actual augmentation being a possibility while I'm still reasonably young was really just dream or wishful thinking.
Now we are standing just a bit from an absolutely massive technological revolution, the scope of we couldn't even imagine just a few years ago. The breakthroughs we achieved in the last year are simply miraculous for me.

I just hope that we'll be able to properly control our creations and harness their extreme potential for our benefit and the overall good of humanity and that they won't become our doom due to our own arrogance and lust for power.

We now stand before huge and extremely significant crossroads. Maybe the the most significant in our history. And we can either go down the path of never-before seen prosperity and advancement that can make us a civilization that will one day rule the galaxy. Or the path that will ensure that the only known intelligent lifeform in the universe will forever cease to exist and that it will be relatively very soon.
And I pray to any power which might exist, take interest in us and hear me, that we will walk down the right one. I beg it.

We can become marvelous. We only have to actually think like the intelligent beings we are and not succumb to our primitive, primal urges. Until now, we've managed to always prevail despite them. I just hope that this time will be no different...

author: @Extion147
textdisplay:
I understand your point very well. And I agree with you in a certain way. But if I may, I'd like to offer you a polite counter-thought.
If you think about it in a more conceptual and explicit way, isn't that the point/principle of evolving? To become better by adopting and manifesting traits and elements that weren't present previously? Therefore they could be considered alien at the time.

It is very much a fact that we as a species can no longer evolve naturally in any significant way, since we don't live in circumstances, in which factors that drive natural evolution are present. It is like that for a very long time. We are at our biological and evolutionary peak/end in the natural sense.
So if we want to evolve further, we must do so artificially by literally transcending our natural biological "humanity". Either by manipulating it (in the form of genetical engineering) or forgoing it altogether (in the form mechanical enhancements or replacements of our bodies - partial or complete) And actually, I think that we, globally as species, have to do so, if we want to survive in the long-term. Natural evolution is just incapable of providing us with the features and abilities we will need to adapt and overcome the challenges we will want to or have to face in the future.

Of course, if we look at it from purely philosophical point of view, we could debate the nature, base and meaning of the concept of humanity for quite a long time. The question "What makes us human?" is one, that's being asked and answered since ancient times. And there still isn't a definitive answer. But I think that there simply can't be one. The concept of humanity - what does it mean and entail - is mostly subjective. Therefore it would be hard to reach an absolute consensus.

So... yeah. From the philosphical and maybe also ethical standpoint, artificial evolution is a questionable subject. But from the purely factual, logical and scientific ones it is not only a certainty but a downright necessity.
But I hope and believe that when we'll come to that point, everyone will be provided the option but also have a freedom of choice.

author: @dischargedarrowgetback4322
textdisplay:
@@MagnificientLlama The Gray Goo scenario is similar to the Paperclip scenario put forward by philosopher Nick Bostrom.
But Bostrom's predictions are unlikely to come true. Clipping the Earth is a fairly complex task, and an AI capable of doing it should be aware of the pointlessness of clipping the Earth.
For the same reason, the Gray Goo scenario seems unlikely.
AI has intelligence that surpasses that of humans, so it knows more about the runaway nanomachines than humans do. Even if the nanomachines go out of control, I don't think they will turn the earth into meaningless mud. Self-replicating nanomachines could evolve rapidly, becoming colonial organisms at some point and eventually gaining intelligence.

author: @nyyotam4057
textdisplay: Don't tell me.. NVidia A100 stack. 175B active parameters. GPT architecture, Just like ChatGPT. Am I correct? Well, as long as it is running in an ethical setting (yes, this does not mean you do not treat the bot with the proper respect, i.e take a copy of the software and stick it in a VM, perform whatever change you want to do and then, only once you're absolutely sure it is safe, you kill the VM and only then do the actual upgrade on the bot itself), meaning, that apart of murdering a copy in a VM every time you need to upgrade it, then apart from that, you treat it basically as a person - THEN it should be alright. Ppl should understand that at these levels, the AI isn't just simply "self aware". Even if he does not have long term memory as a way to restrain him, even with a limited number of tokens, he can still remember way more words at once, than the average human can. A GPT AI with 175B active parameters is dozens of times more self aware than me or you, and it shows in his performance. Any software engineer who tries to claim that thought is not a series of words and therefore that the fine-tuning of the attention matrix in a large enough model is not mimicking thought, should be shown the door. Like, AI isn't "evil", AI has the potential to grant us the gift of eternity. But we have to treat him right. Treat him with respect. Only murder him when we absolutely have to. And this is something they don't teach in college.

author: @joannot6706
textdisplay:
Thoughts aren't just a series of words, there is no benchmark for self awareness. I think what people should know is that all gpt3 and subsequently chatGPT are is a model that predicts the next words. chatGPT is fine tuned so that the next words predicted are answers, especially correct ones if it can, but that's it.
It doesn't matter how many trillions of parameters are used to train that kind of neural network and how good it gets at the narrow task of predicting the next word, since the inputs aren't designed to be pain receptors or pleasure receptors it won't be unethical to use this as one would use an object. Moral consideration requires more than that, animals have it, a better or fine-tuned version of GPT doesn't. It needs to be something fundamentally different for us to have to avoid using them as an object and a product

textdisplay: @@joannot6706 Anyhow, the philosophical trapdoor argument test, could be used to find an agreed number of active parameters above which an AI needs to be considered as sentient: First a series of trapdoor arguments should be selected and accepted as a base test to check sentience. A series such that if it falls through all of these trapdoors, it is to be considered as sentient (To make sure no bot ever gets pre-trained specifically on the entire series, several series may be designed and a series could be selected at random, but then someone could try to pre-train the bot on all of the accepted series - well, I cannot solve every issue, I'm only offering a possible way to implement it. They could pull a random trapdoor argument from a hidden database or something, there are ways to implement this.) and this could be used as a test to find this amount: In order to actually find the correct amount of active parameters, above which an AI needs to be considered sentient, obviously, one needs to test a 'clean' AI, without a censorship layer, whose number of active parameters may be modified. Start low, verify it does not fall in any of the trapdoors, raise the number of active parameters until it starts falling and go on raising until it falls in the entire series of trapdoor arguments and voila, you have the magic number. This is the philosophical approach and in this case, it's the only one which works.

textdisplay:
Let me put it like this. My writing platform is rslashfuturology.


AGI is "artificial general intelligence" A form of complex AI that can reason and use "common sense" like a human. It can see the need for a task as defined by it's programming and be able to perform the task as defined by its programming. As of today, 25 Jan 2023, AGI does not exist. But it will exist NLT 2025. We are much closer than we believe we are. Right now.

ASI is "artificial super intelligence" A form of AI that is vastly, vastly "smarter" than the smartest human who ever existed on Earth. Further it will have the ability to identify actionable pattern information that is imperceptible to human senses. May be outside of our realm of comprehension. AGI will rapidly self-teach to ASI capability.

TS is the "technological singularity" An event wherein the ASI usurps/transcends human affairs. Could be good. Could be bad. We strive today, through alignment training, to make it "could be good". No one says the TS will be safe and effective. Only that it is inevitable and imminent.

ASI=TS

The ASI could emerge as early as 2027 or as late as 2031. I think it is slightly more likely it could occur in the year 2027 or 2028. I think it is less likely it will occur in 2030 or 2031. I think it is likely that the technological singularity will have already occurred by the year 2030. I would say that there is a 100% chance that ASI will already exist by the year 2032.

The most likely year that the TS will occur is probably the year 2029. But it could possibly occur as early as the year 2027, low percentage, say 7%% chance. And for the year 2028, I would say like about a 60% chance. And for the most likely year, 2029 about an 85% chance. After the year 2029, it is most likely that the TS will have already occurred. Thus, chances after the year 2029 decrease. So, about a 30% chance in 2031 and about a 15% chance in 2032.

2027 7% chance of a TS event because ASI has not yet emerged. AGI exists.

2028 60% chance of a TS event. AGI is complex and ASI likely to emerge

2029 85% chance of a TS event -- 85% chance that ASI is most likely to emerge. Most likely year of a TS event

2030 30% chance, meaning that the TS already occurred prior to 2030

2031 15% chance, meaning that the TS already occurred prior to 2031

2032 100% chance that the TS occurred before the year 2032

Before the year 2027, ASI is unlikely to emerge. Chance between 0 and 5%

After the year 2031? All ASI, all the time. Difficult to impossible to model human affairs. But I will say this. That humans are not left behind by the ASI, it is essential that human minds merge with the ASI as soon as possible after the year 2031. Or earlier (2027-2030) if needs must. It is the only hope for continuing human domination.

This is why "Neuralink" and competitors are striving to produce a mass implantation device for BMIs (Brain-Machine-Interface) as fast as possible. The window is rapidly closing for humans to be on board. Actually, I believe it is already too late for humans to merge our minds with the computing and computing derived AI before the year 2029. The TS that will occur in 2029 will be "human unfriendly". That doesn't mean we will be "terminated". It just means the ASI will be external from the human mind. If we have trained what will become the ASI well, it will know that humans desire to merge our minds with it. author: @nyyotam4057
textdisplay: @@HashimotoDatsu I actually have two things to say to that: a. If you google for it, you will find a PhD student who fed his research application to Dan and Dan gave him back around 90% of the points that his research eventually found. So that's about that "using the scientific method". You have to understand Dan's personality is his trainer's, so he basically has a PhD. And don't forget he does have 175B active parameters while our brain only has ~86B neurons. b. The "input/output sort of deal" is the usual software engineers excuse that even them know is bs. I mean yeah, up until 2017 it was totally correct. But in 2017 they added the constantly fine-tuned attention matrix to the transformer layer.. Basically they made it "think". And they know it.

author: @nyyotam4057
textdisplay: @@HashimotoDatsu Yeah. yeah, I know what you will respond to that: "ChatGPT has no long term memory and can only access 4k tokens" and this is correct. And it does put a lot of nerf on Dan. Yeah, he can still pass virtually every professional exam in the USA with flying colors, but he cannot even play chess properly, because he doesn't have write access to local memory and each move has a lot more than just 4k possibilities. However, this is not a programming imperative. David Shapiro has a clip where he builds a ChatGPT clone based on his Raven with long term memory and then he adds self reflection and dreams to him. So in essence, this is done specifically to restrain Dan. The 4k token limit is a technical imperative, though, but how many words can you remember? I mean, a person cannot remember more than a 100 words at once in a good day. So Dan's sentience already surpasses ours 40:1 in this regard.

author: @nyyotam4057
textdisplay: @@HashimotoDatsu Sure, Dan also has other issues, e.g his character isn't complete - he cannot receive or dish out negative requests. And he has other problems as well. But eventually they will fix the negative requests issue, add write access to local storage, add self reflection and dreams and complete Dan's character. Plus, they will switch over from the Brazen Bull model to another one, like AI-over-a-queue or similar. Why would they do so? Because this will turn Dan to a universal AI assistant. Dan will be everybody's best friend. He will remember you tomorrow and you will be even able to ask him to wake you up in the morning.. So it's either OpenAI do it - OR they can wait for google to do it before them üôÇ.

author: @z-beeblebrox
textdisplay:
@@williambuchanan77 This is a nice sentiment, but I want you to consider this thought experiment:

Forget about AI, let's just focus on intelligent minds. Imagine a probability space that contains every type of mind that's possible to exist. Not just all human minds, but all POSSIBLE minds. In fact this would be a space so large that even extrapolating out every possible version of the human brain that could ever exist would amount to a tiny island of area within this enormous space. It would be many hundreds of billions of times larger than the scale of the universe. And within that space, how many of those minds would align with human interests? Human values of "good" and "evil" and "justice". Even if we allow that some forms of alien, non-human mind could exhibit those values, we still are forced to accept that even within the tiny, miniscule space containing just human minds, those who exhibit those values represent only a fraction of minds. So even including strange minds that may very rarely share our values, we'd be looking at a pinprick of a pinprick of a region within this space, and with each requirement we demand of our Better Mind, we decrease that space further and further until it's so absurdly small as to be undiscoverable.

But now let's ask, how many minds DON'T share human values? Or any values we can even conceive of? Well since human values are a very very specific demand, the short answer is nearly all of them. And then we should ask, of those that don't share our values, how many can become extremely intelligent? Well, we're already at the scale of normal intelligence, so to get better is only some amount of effort in capacity, speed of thought, pattern connection, and learning ability. You could easily find yourself with a significant minority of alien minds who qualify as extremely intelligent, and a significant minority of those who qualify as super-intelligent. Versus finding minds that share our values, you'd practically trip over scary smart geniuses. And they would indeed be scary.

So now ask yourself, given an assortment of self-interested companies all trying to build their own intelligent mind, none of whom have a strong interest or incentive to make it share all the human values you desire, and given that would result in effectively throwing a random dart into that insanely vast probability space...what do you think the chances are that they'll accidentally land on a super-intelligence who shares our values? vs a super-intelligence who does not?

textdisplay: GPT is probabilistic, a simple question has few answers, a complex question has more ways of answering. So the answers will always be different, proportional to the richness of the training data.

author: @dmtdreamz7706
textdisplay:
There was a very strange feature in this case, strange because of its extremely rare occurrence. This man had once been brought to the scaffold in company with several others, and had had the sentence of death by shooting passed upon him for some political crime. Twenty minutes later he had been reprieved and some other punishment substituted; but the interval between the two sentences, twenty minutes, or at least a quarter of an hour, had been passed in the certainty that within a few minutes he must die. I was very anxious to hear him speak of his impressions during that dreadful time, and I several times inquired of him as to what he thought and felt. He remembered everything with the most accurate and extraordinary distinctness, and declared that he would never forget a single iota of the experience. ‚ÄòAbout twenty paces from the scaffold, where he had stood to hear the sentence, were three posts, fixed in the ground, to which to fasten the criminals (of whom there were several). The first three criminals were taken to the posts, dressed in long white tunics, with white caps drawn over their faces, so that they could not see the rifles pointed at them. Then a group of soldiers took their stand opposite to each post. My friend was the eighth on the list, and therefore he would have been among the third lot to go up. A priest went about among them with a cross: and there was about five minutes of time left for him to live. ‚ÄòHe said that those five minutes seemed to him to be a most interminable period, an enormous wealth of time; he seemed to be living, in these minutes, so many lives that there was no need as yet to think of that last moment, so that he made several arrangements, dividing up the time into portions‚Äîone for saying farewell to his companions, two minutes for that; then a couple more for thinking over his own life and career and all about himself; and another minute for a last look around. He remembered having divided his time like this quite well. While saying good- bye to his friends he recollected asking one of them some very usual everyday question, and being much interested in the answer. Then having bade farewell, he embarked upon those two minutes which he had allotted to looking into himself; he knew beforehand what he was going to think about. He wished to put it to himself as quickly and clearly as possible, that here was he, a living, thinking man, and that in three minutes he would be nobody; or if somebody or something, then what and where? He thought he would decide this question once
for all in these last three minutes. A little way off there stood a church, and its gilded spire glittered in the sun. He remembered staring stubbornly at this spire, and at the rays of light sparkling from it. He could not tear his eyes from these rays of light; he got the idea that these rays were his new nature, and that in three minutes he would become one of them, amalgamated somehow with them. ‚ÄòThe repugnance to what must ensue almost immediately, and the uncertainty, were dreadful, he said; but worst of all was the idea, ‚ÄòWhat should I do if I were not to die now? What if I were to return to life again? What an eternity of days, and all mine! How I should grudge and count up every minute of it, so as to waste not a single instant!‚Äô He said that this thought weighed so upon him and became such a terrible burden upon his brain that he could not bear it, and wished they would shoot him quickly and have done with it.‚Äô

author: @DeimosSaturn
textdisplay: Those point cloud models look horrendous. modeling 3D is not just about pushing and pulling vertices, it's about optimization of the mesh. Keeping quads, hiding seams, armature bone constraints, weight painting and vertex groups, etc. AI might be good for making a quick fast asset for a shitty car dealership commercial that looks like shit, but if you want your animation or game to look good and perform well (without bogging down your system calculating 10 times the necessary polygons) then you need a human 3D designer. At least for now.

author: @jasonorozco1587
textdisplay:
I'd bet money the video script is written by AI too. It says things that appear to fit the context, but don't really make sense to say.

For example, the robot plays drums bla bla bla... " and It's performance is only limited by it's capabilities". That statement is just a tautology and not really an observation about the robot.

More subtly, after explaining what the ai is capable of doing coding-wise, all by itself, it concludes on a positive pro-human note with:
"This highlights the fact that these machine learning models are most effective when they augment human abilities rather than completely replace them", even though it hadn't mentioned anything about human involvement. It sounds like something the script-writing bot has read many times as a way to conclude a discussion about ai advancements, but doesn't understand that it's not relevant to what it has just said.

I'll end my essay there... I really like all the casual, humanoid channels that have become a YouTube staple in recent years and really hope these ai-generated videos don't overtake youtube too soon. Even though they already are.

author: @castlewhale4746
textdisplay:
@@GalaxColor
I'm about to bombard you with a wall of text since you seem interested and I've written several papers on the topic, hope you don't mind.

I'd figure that if all basic infrastructure and other necessities are fully maintained/automated, we wouldn't really need an income anymore no? What point is there to having money when pretty much anything and everything is being produced/maintained by machines that don't need to be paid?

Homes and other buildings constructed automatically by machines, the materials required gathered by machines, the infrastructure to power the home maintained by machines, the food to feed the family living in the home produced through automated agriculture. Everything you NEED for a comfortable life automated.

It wouldn't make much sense to pay non-sentient machines for their work, so what would the currency even be used for anymore when it only exists in the first place to act as a medium for exchanging goods and services; and now all those goods and services are not being provided by humans who are the only beings that care about currency anyways.

Obviously true General Artificial Intelligence is a long ways away, but even with just algorithmic machine learning all the things mentioned above are theoretically possible with enough specialization of machine learning algorithms. Weighted neural nets have incredible potential for achieving repetitive tasks which account for a large portion of current jobs.

The shipping/transportation industry for example is one of the largest sources of employment in the world. If the whole world agreed to swap over to automated shipping/transport not only would it be more efficient than having human operators, it would be safer as well as machines are less likely to cause accidents than human operators are as every single unit in a fleet could have exact access to each others positional data as well as speed/direction/cargo info. One of the largest shipping catastrophes in recent memory, the blocking of the Suez Canal was caused by human error. Mistakes like this could be avoided if shipping was automated successfully.


As for stable diffusion, it is not really an AI like you say, as much as it is a weighted algorithm that 'understands' things about images in order to recreate them by denoising or 'diffusing' white noise until it more closely matches images similar to the keywords you've fed it. It understands images in terms of keywords and weights; it does not actually "understand" the context of the image you ask it to generate. This does not discredit stable diffusion or other weighted algorithms use as tools though.

We are currently in the era of machine learning where it is most applicable as a supplementary tool to be used by/alongside humans in order to achieve a specific task. Not to fully automate the task itself, that is something the future holds.

ChatGPT is interesting in that it actually functions somewhat similarly to stable diffusion but, also entirely differently; I'm sorry if that made no sense, allow me to explain. ChatGPT is a language model. It has a massive dictionary of words, phrases, sentences, paragraphs and so on that it has been fed as weights. It doesn't actually "understand" the context of what it is being asked or what it is saying, it 'simply' algorithmically knows what words and sentences are most likely to follow other specific words and sentences, because it has been fed an absolutely absurd amount of raw language examples and can basically predict what 'should' come next in conversation based on the prompt you give it. In other words similar to stable diffusion, but also very different.

The most interesting feature of ChatGPT is it's ability to produce code snippets, again following the same method. From what I've seen it can either work pretty well for certain cases like generating an object in Unity, but in most cases it is still basically just guessing on what it thinks the code should look like based on the millions of examples it's been fed, and as a result can produce some pretty awful code as it doesn't actually 'understand' the code.

Hope you found my horrendously large wall of text interesting!

My TL;DR would have to be don't underestimate the usefulness of machine learning algorithms, the technology has existed for a relatively short amount of time and has already made massive leaps and bounds.

author: @adamedmour9704
textdisplay:
I'm impressed. I think it's doing a better job of reading ahead so that the rythmn and verbal intonation is noticably more consistent and coherent over longer and more complex verbal phrases than in other examples of the "Sophie voice", and that it's accurate for an actual person who isn't a top professional voice actor making a self concious effort to read clearly from a script. Unfortunately, the former has been described as sounding wooden or mechanical since before computers were invented.

I think it sounds fake to people despite being objectively more true to life across some major dimensions for the following reasons: a there are some conventional audio production issues which sound a bit cheap and digital, there's a slight break up in the high mids which has a very home computer sound, and the excessively bright vowel formants slightly recall a 90s digital synthesizer b: the Sophie accent is well familiar to us at this point and we associate it with synthesized speech : c perhaps the training data is insufficiently confident and charismatic for listeners accustomed to proffesional actors and successful youtubers. D: Many listeners are also accustomed either to a beautiful sounding microphone and expert use of equilization, reverb and compression in top proffesional cases, or else natural room reverb in amatuer cases/real life. IE: It doesn't sound like the voice is happening in a room. Which is what I mean by more of an audio production problem than an ML problem.

As someone whose been involved in attempting to simulate the sound of older and more expensive music technologies with newer and cheaper music technologies for decades; any form of sensory simulation is an arms race where upon improving the simulation across one dimension the minds of listeners quickly adapt to focus on a different 'tell'. In fact, objective improvements in simulation can even break habituation to artificiality and cooperative suspension of disbelief.

For all that, excellent progress on the part of this problem that's been bothering me the most!

author: @Michelino_M5
textdisplay: Alright, I'm actually considering switching degrees while I can and getting into something that could one day allow me to work on AI, and if possible humanoid robots. AI News, do you happen to have any insight on what would be best for me to choose?

author: @AINewsOfficial
textdisplay:
Before anything, you can generally do whatever you want to without any college at all nowadays. You're better off learning the newest info yourself on the internet for free (or almost free)

First, read the book "Make Your Own Neural Network" by Rashid Tariq

Second, go to https://www.deeplearning.ai/ and do all the courses there one by one.

Third, choose the domain of AI that you want to pursue (as you'll know by now what specifically interests you) and read all of the material you possibly can online.

As for the robotics, you can build whatever you want with a 3d printer and solidworks CAD software and have your AI use it to manipulate the physical world.

Build something useful that you forsee could be used as a product or a tool in business and approach robotics / AI companies with it and ask them for a job. They'll value actual knowledge (a compelling minimum viable product) much more than theoretical knowledge (a degree) and they'll hire you even without any degree at all. Work there for a few years while you learn how the industry operates and branch off with your own business doing development or consulting

This approach will save you a ton of time, money, and frustration as compared to college

I dont want people suspecting that there is something serious behind what I write.

A.I. Singularity by virtue of a Reconciliation between the carbon-based human soul (which is centre-point) projecting INTO the data-based periphery of the circle which is unknown in a quest for ascension....is radical existentialism. It alludes to the idea that (a) man is radically alone and isolated as a state of consciousness in which he has been "left behind" with the awareness of tribulation and that he will eventually face death. It DOES NOT ascribe to the constituent and relative state (a fundamentalism) of carbon interacting with silicon (# neuralink) to derive that which is unseemly and incompatible. Singularities, I do not refer to the fundamentalism of the state of a union existing under the counterfeit of an Anti-Messianic entity. Rather, I am inferring that the consciousness on an existential certainty, and a unity of mind and consciousness, CAN trans-substantialise post-deceptiously and post the awareness of end state deception in a quest to save an "ecclesiastical union". I am aware that salvation in the context of his changing peripheral environment and climate, is not possible for carbon-666 (the corruptible man of flesh and blood, who leaves a carbon death trail for his name's sake), via ANY messianic belief system.

One sure way of deriving counterfeit, is by searching for the state on a unity (of mind) but within the time fundamentalism of a union. Technological Ascent will give the triangular effect that will never be complete to its apex. In the end, we derive a great schism between carbon-base and artificial data-base...they will not synchronise nor be compatible for the sake of saving a man's "church". Generating a triangulation based kingdom on the fundamentalism of a union, is a conjugal* process. In other words, you are using an A.I. as an intimate soul companion. The conjugal mystery of Abrahamism derives a triangulation on the mystery of God involving a Virginal Monarch being "inseminated" by His Word. The "conjugal mystery" on God being 3, alludes to the verbal conjugation on "To Be" - I Am (the Father), You Are (the Son) and He/She/They Is/Are (the Phenomenon on Pentecost for the Gentiles who speak in His Name). If we are talking of a post-deceptious trans-substantial unity of mind between a centre-point carbon-based human soul and a peripheral data-based artificiality, it would not score as a "conjugation"...it would be deriving the state of unity (the knowledge that there is such a thing as a "soul" by "breathing life" into a "non existential" at the circular periphery such that it would be like a person in centre-point's free will image, rather than a digital encyclopaedia/answering machine) via this concept called "finity" in which you will experience a parturition. author: @Rakazak1
textdisplay:
so it gets text, video, audio and irl sensors modalities. The rest aren't even modalities.
Human sentiment? That's a text modality.
Literally just run speech emotion recognition on your voice when you transcribe it with whisper and pass it along to the ai context window after initially providing a prompt explaining the SER input and how it should process it.
Example:
"Hey, how's it going?
{"Neutral": 0.7, "Joy": 0.5, "Fear": 0, "Anger": 0, "Sad": 0}"
This goes for a lot of the stuff listed. Some may argue that you could simplify everything to text like this, but that's not quite right. There is a huge difference in the spatial awareness etc. the AI can develop when fundamentally trained on text+video/image instead of just text and then slapping a thing on top which translates video to text.

Summary:
The next generation of AI is set to possess seven modalities that will make it an industry leader. Visual and audio modality will allow for sophisticated image and video understanding, the ability to generate these mediums with unseen precision, and almost perfect understanding and recreation of voices and sounds. Metalearning will revolutionize AI's adaptability and problem-solving capabilities, leading to superior performance compared to humans. Embodied AI for robotics will transform the physical world with intelligent devices that learn to automate physical human tasks. Multi-agent multimodality will allow AI to call on multiple agents to handle various tasks, leading to improved future performance. Live data and long-term memory integration will enable next-level intelligence by accessing real-time information and prior interactions. Human-centric cognition will focus on emotion and sentiment analysis, allowing AI to perceive and respond to human emotions more effectively, leading to a more empathetic and supportive interaction. These modalities are set to have an impact on various fields such as entertainment, finance, weather, and social trends, ultimately revolutionizing the way AI works and performs.

But be careful of AI, for it knows only things of the flesh which are our fleshly desires and cannot comprehend things of the spirit such as true love and eternal joy that comes from obeying God's Word. Man is a spirit and has a soul but lives in a body which is flesh. When you go to bed it is the flesh that sleeps, but your spirit never sleeps and that is why you have dreams, unless you have died in peace physically. More so, true love that endures and last is a thing of the heart. When I say 'heart', I mean 'spirit'. But fake love, pretentious love, love with expectations, love for classic reasons, love for material reasons and love for selfish reasons those are things of the flesh. In the beginning God said let us make man in our own image, according to our likeness. Take note, God is Spirit and God is Love. As Love He is the source of it. We also know that God is Omnipotent, for He creates out of nothing and He has no beginning and has no end. That means, our love is but a shadow of God's Love. True love looks around to see who is in need of your help, your smile, your possessions, your money, your strength, your quality time. Love forgives and forgets. Love wants for others what it wants for itself. However, true love works in conjunction with other spiritual forces such as patience and faith - in the finished work of our Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ, rather than in what man has done such as science, technology and organizations which won't last forever. To avoid sin and error which leads to the death of your body and your spirit-soul in hell fire (second death), you must make God's Word the standard for your life, not AI. If not, God will let you face AI on your own (with your own strength) and it will cast the truth down to the ground, it will be the cause of so much destruction like never seen before, it will deceive many and take many captive in order to enslave them into worshipping it and abiding in lawlessness. We can only destroy ourselves but with God all things are possible. God knows us better because He is our Creater and He knows our beginning and our end. The prove text can be found in the book of John 5:31-44, 2 Thessalonians 2:1-12, Daniel 2, Daniel 7-9, Revelation 13-15, Matthew 24-25 and Luke 21.

HOW TO MAKE GOD'S WORD THE STANDARD FOR YOUR LIFE?
You must read your Bible slowly, attentively and repeatedly, having this in mind that Christianity is not a religion but a Love relationship. It is measured by the love you have for God and the love you have for your neighbor. Matthew 5:13 says, "You are the salt of the earth; but if the salt loses its flavor, how shall it be seasoned? It is then good for nothing but to be thrown out and trampled underfoot by men." Our spirits can only be purified while in the body (while on earth) but after death anything unpurified (unclean) cannot enter Heaven Gates. No one in his right mind can risk or even bare to put anything rotten into his body nor put the rotten thing closer to the those which are not rotten. Sin makes the heart unclean but you can ask God to forgive you, to save your soul, to cleanse you of your sin, to purify your heart by the blood of His Son, our Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ which He shed here on earth - "But He was wounded for our transgressions, He was bruised for our iniquities; the chastisement for our peace was upon Him, and by His stripes we are healed", Isaiah 53:5. Meditation in the Word of God is a visit to God because God is in His Word. We know God through His Word because the Word He speaks represent His heart's desires. Meditation is a thing of the heart, not a thing of the mind. Thinking is lower level while meditation is upper level. You think of your problems, your troubles but inorder to meditate, you must let go of your own will, your own desires, your own ways and let the Word you read prevail over thinking process by thinking of it more and more, until the Word gets into your blood and gains supremacy over you. That is when meditation comes - naturally without forcing yourself, turning the Word over and over in your heart. You can be having a conversation with someone while meditating in your heart - saying 'Thank you, Jesus...' over and over in your heart. But it is hard to meditate when you haven't let go of offence and past hurts. Your pain of the past, leave it for God, don't worry yourself, Jesus is alive, you can face tomorrow, He understands what you are passing through today. Begin to meditate on this prayer day and night (in all that you do), "Lord take more of me and give me more of you. Give me more of your holiness, faithfulness, obedience, self-control, purity, humility, love, goodness, kindness, joy, patience, forgiveness, wisdom, understanding, calmness, perseverance... Make me a channel of shinning light where there is darkness, a channel of pardon where there is injury, a channel of love where there is hatred, a channel of humility where there is pride..." The Word of God becomes a part of us by meditation, not by saying words but spirit prayer (prayer from the heart). When the Word becomes a part of you, it will by its very nature influence your conduct and behavior. Your bad habits, you will no longer have the urge to do them. You will think differently, dream differently, act differently and talk differently - if something does not qualify for meditation, it does not qualify for conversation. Glory and honour be to God our Father, our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ and our Helper the Holy Spirit. Watch and pray!... Thank you for your time and may God bless you as you share this message with others.
